text:
Warpcast Spam labels are improving 

Our new system uses LLMs to make better decisions. It will make fewer mistakes in both directions and will prevent legitimate users from getting the spam label. 

We expect fewer users to get the spam label as a result of this change. It may take a few weeks to roll out fully.

A few people have pointed out that they have neither an X or a Github. We're making changes to support them:

1. If you're active and earning rewards, you won't have to connect socials. Exact threshold TBD. 

2. If you're a brand new user, you can pay to skip connecting socials.

3. We're also going to add more socials and onchain verifications over time to make this easier.

cast.text:
Farcaster Verifications are coming soon

Verify your account by connecting two socials (X, Phone or GitHub) and holding $25 in your wallet. 

Verified accounts are less likely to get the spam label and show up higher in the feed, replies and search. 

They are necessary to earn weekly rewards and qualify for airdrops

text:
We‚Äôre planning to launch a new, optional ‚ÄúPro‚Äù protocol subscription

1. At launch, subscribers will have a Pro badge on their profile

2. Subscription will be onchain and part of the protocol. 100% of the proceeds go to casters / developers in weekly rewards. This in addition to the existing $25K+ a week in rewards. 

3. Planning to add longer casts (10K characters) and up to 4 images per cast for pro subscribers (needs a protocol change). Additional features over time.

4. $120 a year / $10 a month‚Ä®
Why are we doing this?

- The protocol needs to find long-term revenue source that can continue fund caster and developer rewards beyond any one company. ‚Ä®
- We originally thought storage fees could be that, but we‚Äôve realized that storage fees should be essentialy free to help growth.‚Ä®
- So we‚Äôre trying an opt-in pro subscription as another model

Why now?

- Figuring out a long-term revenue model that works will allow us to double down on investing in growth

html.ogDescription:
You're invited to PizzaDAO's 5th annual Global Pizza Party in honor of Bitcoin Pizza Day.

It's been 15 years since May 22, 2010, when Laszlo Hanyecz bought two pizzas for 10,000 bitcoin. Today, 10,000 bitcoin buys a lot more than two pizzas!

We think that's a big deal. So in partnership with our co-hosts at Digital Spenders Club and Stand with Crypto, plus friends at Logos Network, Story, Sui, For All Mankind, The Park and Base, we're throwing our 5th Global Pizza Party! 

We're expecting over 25,000 total attendees across more than 400 cities worldwide.

Networking via Icebreaker and Media by CryptoSapiens - your image might go on...
